    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We are hitting several limits now using json, there might be [possible workarounds](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/29175877/json-stringify-throws-rangeerror-invalid-string-length-for-huge-objects) but those are potentially really slow and still require a lot of memory.\r\n\r\nThe error is thrown during serialization but the message it definitely not great, should be more descriptive but proper solution is to support ssz for all apis (https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/pull/6080) and follow spec (e.g. set all metadata headers).",
